-- Boutique investment bank Moelis' shares rise 9 pct in debut
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Wed Apr 16, 2014 09:57AM EDT
-- None



April 16 (Reuters) - Shares of Moelis & Co <MC.N> rose about 9 percent in their debut, valuing the boutique investment bank at about $1.40 billion.

The company raised about $163 million, after its offering was priced at $25, below the expected price range of $26-$29 per share. [ID:nL3N0N74GO] Moelis, founded and led by veteran Wall Street investment banker Ken Moelis, is offering 6.5 million shares of Class A common stock. It initially planned to offer 7.3 million shares. Moelis' shares opened at $27 on the New York Stock Exchange on Wednesday and touched a high of $27.22 in early trading.